wikipedia_page.main: George Yvon (February 15, 1887 – November 20, 1957) was a British diver who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics. He was born in France, and died in Great Britain.In 1912 he competed in both the men's 10 metre platform, in which he placed fifth, as well as the men's plain high events.
